# Feature Implementation Workflow

Follow these steps **in order** for every feature.

## 1. Understand

- Read the GitHub issue thoroughly (`gh issue view <number>`)
- Identify acceptance criteria and edge cases
- If anything is unclear, ask before coding

## 2. Branch

- Create a branch from up-to-date `main` (see github-issues rule for naming)

## 3. Implement

- Work in small, focused increments
- Each increment should leave the codebase in a working state
- Do not change unrelated code in the same branch

## 4. Test

- Run existing tests before committing
- Add tests for new behavior when applicable
- Verify manually if no automated tests exist

## 5. Commit

- Commit after each logical unit of work (see commit-conventions rule)
- **ALWAYS commit current work before switching to another feature or branch**
- Never leave uncommitted changes when changing context

## 6. Push & PR

- Push the branch: `git push -u origin HEAD`
- Open a PR linked to the issue: `gh pr create --title "..." --body "Closes #<number>"`
- Wait for review — do not merge your own PR without approval
